.. contents::

Description
===========


General information
===================

- **Author**: Tuomas Räsänen (tuos) <tuos@codegrove.org>
- **Homepage**: http://codegrove.org/notetaker/
- **License**: GPLv3+ (see COPYING for details)
- **Version**: 0.1

Runtime requirements
====================

Build requirements
==================

Supported devices
=================

- Pegasus Tablet Mobile NoteTaker M210

Downloading
===========

- Ubuntu package: https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/notetaker
- Tarball is available at: http://codegrove.org/notetaker/releases/notetaker-0.1.tar.gz
- Tarballs of every release at: http://codegrove.org/notetaker/releases/
- Latest sources from public git-repository: http://github.com/tuos/notetaker/ ::

    git clone git://github.com/tuos/notetaker.git

Installing
==========

Ubuntu
------

The recommended way to install notetaker is to
`add it's PPA to your system <https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove>`_.
This allows you to treat notetaker as any other Ubuntu package.

Other systems
-------------

The install-procedure adheres the "standard"::

  ./configure
  make && make install

Configuration & Run
===================

